        <num>CCP 284</num>
        <heading>284.  Judicial powers of district court clerk</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 284.  Judicial powers of district court clerk
The clerk of a district court may render and sign default judgments or judgments by
confession in cases where the jurisdiction of the court is concurrent with that of justices of
the peace, as provided in Article 5011.
Amended by</p>
